# DOC-MAP — {{PROJECT_NAME}} reference index (the meta-KB)

> **What this is:** a router, not a summary. One line per curated reference doc — *what it is* and
> *when to read it* — so an agent (or a human) can find the right doc fast and read it **on demand**
> instead of loading everything up front. Detail lives in the linked docs; this file never duplicates
> their content.
>
> **How to use it:** when a task touches an area, open the doc(s) for that area first. Heavy reference
> docs should be read by a **dispatched subagent** that returns only the conclusion (see the root
> `CLAUDE.md` harness) so the main thread's context stays lean.
>
> **Discipline:** this index and `UI_PAGE_GUIDE.md` are kept honest by
> [`scripts/check_doc_coverage.py`](../../scripts/check_doc_coverage.py): every live route must appear
> in the page guide, and every curated reference doc below should be indexed here (orphan = warning;
> a link to a missing file = hard failure). It runs in the pre-push gate.

## Read first (orientation order)

1. `CLAUDE.md` — project laws, the dev harness, project specifics. Always loaded.
2. `UI_PAGE_GUIDE.md` — **every UI page → endpoints → DB objects** (frontend repos). The first stop for
   any UI or full-stack task.
3. Area `CLAUDE.md` files — load automatically when you work in that folder.

